import { useEffect, useState } from 'react'
import {Route , Routes} from 'react-router-dom'
import {Home , About , Serveces , LoginForm , EmployeDash ,
        UserAdd , UpdateUser , AdminDashboard , Loading , Customer ,
        CreateUserAdmin, AdminRequireAuth , EmployeeRequireAuth , EmpShow , CurrencyRate ,
      CreateBranch,}
    from './components/import.js' 
    import MonyTransfer from './components/employeDashboard/MonyTransfer.js'
    import DepositMony from './components/AdminDashboard/adminComponents/DepositMony.js'
const App = ()=>{
  const [loading , setLoading] = useState(false);
  useEffect(()=>{
    setLoading(true)
    setTimeout(()=>{
      setLoading(false)
    },2000)
  },[])
  return(
    <>
    {
      loading?
      <Loading />
      :
      <Routes>
      <Route path='/' element={<Home />} />
      <Route path='about' element={<About />} />
      <Route path='service' element={<Serveces />} />
      <Route path='currencyRates' element={<CurrencyRate />} />
      <Route path='login' element={<LoginForm />} />
      <Route element={<EmployeeRequireAuth />}>
      <Route path='employeeDashboard' element={<EmployeDash />}>
          <Route path='userAdd' element={<UserAdd />}/>
          <Route path='userUpdate' element={<UpdateUser />} />
          <Route path='userDelete' />
          <Route path='usersShow' />
          <Route path='monyTransfer'element={<MonyTransfer/>}  />

      </Route>
      </Route>
      <Route element={<AdminRequireAuth />}>
      <Route path='adminDashboard' element={<AdminDashboard />}>
        <Route path='CreateUser' element={<CreateUserAdmin />} />
        <Route path='employeesShow' element={<EmpShow />} />
        <Route path='createbranch' element={<CreateBranch />} />
        <Route path='monyTransfer'element={<MonyTransfer/>}  />

      </Route>
      </Route>
      <Route path='load' element={<Loading />} />
      <Route path='form' element={<LoginForm />} />
      <Route path='/customerDashbaord' element={<Customer />} />
    </Routes>
    }
    </>
    
  )
}
export default App;
